%% Diagram: Agent execution states under [[CanBlock]] and the wait/notify contract
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Running
    Running --> Idle: execution context stack empties
    Idle --> Running: host invokes a queued Job

    Running --> Blocked: Atomics.wait\n(only when [[CanBlock]] = true)
    Blocked --> Running: Atomics.notify on same address\nor timeout
    Blocked --> [*]: agent terminated

    Running --> Throws: Atomics.wait called when\n[[CanBlock]] = false (TypeError)

    note right of Blocked
        Spec §9.8 Forward Progress:
        an agent may not block another agent
        except via explicit blocking APIs.
        Browser main-thread agents have
        [[CanBlock]] = false — only Workers
        and Node main thread can suspend.
    end note
